    <title>HTML Formatting Tags Example</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
        }
        h1 {
            color: darkblue;
        }
        p {
            line-height: 1.6;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <h1>HTML Formatting Tags Example</h1>

    <h2>Various Formatting Tags</h2>

    <p>This is a <strong>strong text</strong> and this is a <b>bold text</b>.</p>
    <p>This is a <big>big text</big> and this is a <small>small text</small>.</p>
    <p>This text is <em>emphasized</em> and this is <i>italic</i>.</p>
    <p>Here is some <mark>highlighted text</mark>.</p>
    <p>This text is <u>underlined</u>.</p>
    <p>This is <tt>teletype text</tt> for monospace representation.</p>
    <p>This text is <del>stricken through</del> and this text is <ins>inserted</ins>.</p>
    <p>Here is a <strike>strikethrough text</strike>.</p>
    <p>Superscript : (2)<sup>3</sup> = 8</p>
    <p>Subscript : H<sub>2</sub>O</p>

</body>
